All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
Main
The Main class processes tasks based on user input and prioritizes them according to the user IDs.
MyPriorityQueue<T>
This interface represents a priority queue, where elements are ordered based on their natural ordering or by a comparator provided at queue construction time.
MyTask
The MyTask class represents a task that is associated with a user and has a unique ID.
MyUser
The MyUser class represents a user with a unique ID and a priority value.
TaskManager
The TaskManager class manages the task queue and the users associated with each task.
TaskScheduler<E>
The TaskScheduler class implements a priority queue using a min-heap data structure.
